Sentencas: A quasi-two-dimensional numerical model is presented for the efficient computation of the steady-state current density, species concentration, and temperature distributions in planar solid oxide fuel cell stacks.
Titulo: A quasi-two-dimensional electrochemistry modeling tool for planar solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: The model reduction techniques, engineering approximations, and numerical procedures used to simulate the stack physics while maintaining adequate computational speed are discussed.
Titulo: A quasi-two-dimensional electrochemistry modeling tool for planar solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: The results of the model for benchmark cases with and without on-cell methane reformation are presented with comparisons to results from other research described in the literature.
Titulo: A quasi-two-dimensional electrochemistry modeling tool for planar solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: Simulations results for a multi-cell stack have also been demonstrated to show capability of the model on simulating cell to cell variation.
Titulo: A quasi-two-dimensional electrochemistry modeling tool for planar solid oxide fuel cell stacks

Sentencas: The capabilities, performance, and scalability of the model for the study of large multi-cell stacks are then demonstrated.
Titulo: A quasi-two-dimensional electrochemistry modeling tool for planar solid oxide fuel cell stacks
